explanation: This solution uses two arrays to count the frequency of each character in both strings. It then calculates the absolute difference between the counts for each character and sums them up. Since each character in one string is replaced by a character from the other string, the total number of steps is half the total difference. This approach has a high efficiency due to its linear time complexity and constant space complexity.

